Here are the key *<https://github.com/OWASP/Nest/milestones|milestones>* that were accepted as part of the OWASP Nest project for *GSoC 2026*:{{ NL }}
  • *OWASP Board Activity Standardization and Data Programmatic Access*: This milestone focuses on standardizing how OWASP Board activities are recorded, structured, and published.{{ NL }}

  • *OWASP Board Candidate Information Transparency and Fact-Checking*: This milestone focuses on improving the transparency, accuracy, and trustworthiness of information related to OWASP board candidates.{{ NL }}

  • *OWASP Community Snapshots:* Creating a summary of activities within OWASP projects, chapters, and events, including new blog posts and news, to keep the community informed about recent developments.{{ NL }}

  • *OWASP Contributor Recognition Program*: This milestone introduces an OWASP-wide Contributor Recognition system in OWASP Nest to make contributions visible, measurable, and shareable across projects and chapters, inspired by community platforms like ContribCard, with potential integration into existing OWASP Nest badges and certificate delivery via services like Certifier.{{ NL }}

  • *OWASP NestBot AI Assistant*: Develop an AI-powered OWASP NestBot Slack assistant that acts as an auto-responder for frequently asked questions, guides users to the appropriate OWASP channels, and handles typical OWASP community queries.{{ NL }}

  • *OWASP Nest Monitoring and Observability*: Implement modern monitoring and observability practices across OWASP Nest infrastructure on AWS to ensure reliability, performance visibility, and proactive issue detection.{{ NL }}

  • *OWASP Nest UI/UX Revamp*: This milestone delivers a comprehensive UI/UX revamp of OWASP Nest to improve usability, accessibility, visual consistency, and the overall contributor experience across the platform.{{ NL }}

  • *OWASP Pulse*: This milestone introduces the OWASP Pulse page in OWASP Nest as a unified, near real-time activity feed that aggregates events across repositories with filters by user, project, repository, and chapter to improve visibility and engagement.{{ NL }}

{{ SECTION_BREAK }}

No other OWASP project received more than 3 slots in 2025, placing OWASP Nest among the most active OWASP initiatives in last year's program. With Google reporting an overall acceptance rate of around 8%, this is a strong reflection of the quality of the proposals and the growing impact of the OWASP Nest project.

